Interface RICededPremiumTransaction

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Bean, com.guidewire.pl.persistence.core.BeanMethods, BundleProvider, java.lang.Comparable<Bean>, Extractable, RICededPremiumTxnAdapter, SimpleEffDated

    @Generated(value="com.guidewire.pl.metadata.codegen.Codegen",

public interface RICededPremiumTransaction
extends SimpleEffDated, Extractable, RICededPremiumTxnAdapter
    RICededPremiumTransaction A delegate for RICededPremiumTransaction, which is an individual ceding calculation done between a direct premium Transaction which insures an RIRisk, and a RIAgreement which reinsures that RIRisk.

      • getCededPremium

        MonetaryAmount getCededPremium()
        Gets the value of the CededPremium field. The amount of premium to cede to the agreement for effective time [EffDate, ExpDate). This value can be negative, as in the case of an offset (certainly) but also in some cases where so much was ceded to prior treaties that what is left is a negative amount.

      • getCededPremiumMarkup

        MonetaryAmount getCededPremiumMarkup()
        Gets the value of the CededPremiumMarkup field. The amount of markup to the agreement for effective time [EffDate, ExpDate). This value can be negative, for the same reasons that CededPremium can be. Normally their signs will match, and the net owed to the reinsurer is CededPremium - Commission.

      • getCedingRate

        java.math.BigDecimal getCedingRate()
        Gets the value of the CedingRate field. The ceding rate used for the calculation. The source of this value depends on the type of agreement. For a proportional agreement, this is the proportion of risk ceded to the agreement; for a non-proportional agreement it is the specified ceding rate.

      • getCommission

        MonetaryAmount getCommission()
        Gets the value of the Commission field. The amount of commission earned from the agreement for effective time [EffDate,ExpDate). This value can be negative, for the same reasons that CededPremium can be. Normally their signs will match, and the net owed to the reinsurer is CededPremium - Commission.

      • getCommissionRate
